$ NastAero VM10: Simply-Supported Plate Modal Analysis (8x8 mesh)
$ Reference: Leissa - Vibration of Plates
$ a=b=1.0m, t=0.01m, E=210GPa (Steel), nu=0.3, rho=7850 kg/m^3
$ 81 nodes (9x9 grid), 64 CQUAD4 elements
$
$ Simply supported: w=0 (DOF 3) on all edges
$ Pin corner node 1 (DOFs 1,2) to prevent rigid body in-plane motion
$
$ Analytical frequencies for simply-supported square plate:
$ f_mn = (pi/(2*a^2)) * sqrt(D/(rho*t)) * (m^2 + n^2)
$ D = E*t^3/(12*(1-nu^2)) = 210e9*1e-6/10.92 = 19230.77 N-m
$ rho*t = 7850*0.01 = 78.5 kg/m^2
$ sqrt(D/(rho*t)) = sqrt(19230.77/78.5) = sqrt(244.97) = 15.652 m/s
$
$ Mode (1,1): f = pi/2 * 15.652 * 2 = 49.16 Hz
$ Mode (1,2): f = pi/2 * 15.652 * 5 = 122.9 Hz
$ Mode (2,1): f = pi/2 * 15.652 * 5 = 122.9 Hz
$ Mode (2,2): f = pi/2 * 15.652 * 8 = 196.6 Hz
$ Mode (1,3): f = pi/2 * 15.652 * 10 = 245.8 Hz
$
SOL 103
CEND
